HEADWORD: Mentomeckelian
<hw>Men`to*meck*e"li*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[1st
<ets>ment</ets>al + <ets>Meckelian</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to the chin and lower jaw.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The bone or cartilage forming the anterior
extremity of the lower jaw in some adult animals and the young of
others.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mentor</ent>⟦br⟧
